    "body": "Agree with @jtattermusch that the ideal solution is to make this easily buildable on windows and the prioritization. \r\n\r\n> 1. make C++ easily buildable on windows (the problem is mostly the openssl and protobuf integration).\r\n> 1. document it properly\r\n> 1. (publishing artifacts is optional - because everyone can build them as easily. Also it is not clear that the artifacts would be usable by everyone based on the compiler and linker options).\r\n\r\nHowever I think that we should have a long term goal of publishing artifacts in some way that's easily catalogued and would not call it optional. This way binaries can be grabbed if people do not want to build. Not being able to cater to every linker/compiler option is OK, since we would have done (1) and (2).\r\n"
  },
