    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "For what it's worth, if you build using `cmake -G \"Visual Studio 14 2015\" -DgRPC_SSL_PROVIDER=\"package\"` works just fine for me after having cloned the zlib/protobuf sources into the appropriate third_party folders.  Only real notes/problems I ran into were having to downgrade OpenSSL to the latest 1.0.n version because of API/artifact changes in 1.1.n and having to disable building the `grpc++_reflection` build because it doesn't seem to generate the .pb.h/.pb.cc files on its own and even when I generate them myself with `protoc` they are missing the `ServerReflection` type.  Granted, took me quite a while to find all of this via the thrilling practice of reading the CMake files, but it wasn't 40 hours of work either.\r\n\r\nOh, I also had to modify the cmake_install paths for zlib by hand, no matter how many different ways I provided `CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX` it just didn't work, mostly because it was hard-coded to the Program Files folder."
  },
